    "quirks": [
      "Responses include pagination fields 'next', 'previous', 'hasNext', and 'hasPrevious' that are not documented but always present.",
      "Numeric strings for 'page' and 'limit' are coerced to integers instead of being rejected.",
      "Sending an empty request body string (no JSON) is treated the same as providing an empty JSON object.",
      "Keyword search is case-insensitive and trims surrounding whitespace; uppercase or padded queries match their lowercase, trimmed equivalents.",
      "Whitespace-only keyword inputs behave like unfiltered searches despite being accepted.",
      "Amounts in the results can be zero or negative, so consumers must handle both signs.",
      "Combining 'keyword' with 'award_type' applies both filters (logical AND)."
    ],
    "risks": [
      "The dataset is extremely large (~18M recipients); high limits or deep pagination can yield large payloads and slower responses.",
      "Enum fields such as 'award_type' and 'order' are case-sensitive, so clients must normalize to lowercase to avoid 400 errors.",
      "Whitespace keywords behave like broad searches, so sanitize user input to prevent unexpectedly wide result sets.",
      "Amounts may be negative or zero, which can break consumers that assume positive summaries.",
      "Recipient names may be null or empty strings; clients should fall back to other identifiers when displaying results."
    ],
    "gaps": [
      "Keyword matching nuances beyond trimming and case-insensitive comparison (e.g., multi-term tokenization, partial-word rules) remain unverified.",
      "The claimed trailing twelve-month aggregation window is assumed from documentation but not independently validated."
    ],
    "tags": [
